value.0: A handsome purple faerie.
<c¥ ¥>Toot</c>

Likely the most reknown and favorite drink of the fey, but also very popular among the elves. A florescent green nectar, created from the juice of various flowers, mixed with honey and other, albeit secret ingredients. This famous nectar is of ancient origin and how to make it is a secret which has been guarded by the faeries since the dawn of time. Many races have tried to replicate it, yet no one ever came close to achieve it.

Caution is advised, this drink is so strong (even though you do not notice it) it is quite famous for putting people to sleep for days if they are not used to it or immune to the effects.
<c È >Feywine</c>

This drink is refreshingly cold and tastes strongly of red fruits. Strawberry clearly being very dominant, along with cherry, raspberry and some fainter tastes which are hard to pick out. While it clearly is alcoholic, the alcohol flavor is not really noticable, as with many fey drinks. Once the sirupy liquid hits your tongue, the sheer amount of flavor almost overwhealms you. It tastes more like the berries used to make it than any berry you have ever tasted, even if it had been riped to perfection.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<c¥  >Red Velvet</c>

A small tart with a delicious berry cream filling. The tart earned its name rightfully so, for the berry cream indeed tastes as the sweet berries to an extreme. 

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<c¥  >Very Berry Tart</c>

A darker liquid which is bubbly and sweet, but it hides quite a kick. Normally Slumberberries cause tiredness and eventually sleep, but some side-effect from being fermented causes it to have the opposite reaction, keeping people awake for a long time.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<c¥ ¥>Slumberberry Cordial</c>

This fried fish has a yellow colour to its flesh and glows very faintly. It has been cooked in a rich garlic butter which leaves small black flecks all over the yellow flesh of the fish. With each bite, you wonder if it could possibly taste any better but then a fe moments later begin to doubt that. 

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<c¥¥ >Black Garlic Butter basted Doubt Trout</c>

A delicious looking crumble, with a sweet blue filling of small, star shape berries which often leaves your mouth feel a little fuzzy in a good way. Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<cPPÿ>Mumble and Bumble Crumble</c>

This fried fish has a yellow colour to its flesh and glows very faintly. It has been cooked in a rich garlic butter which leaves small black flecks all over the yellow flesh of the fish. With each bite, you wonder if it could possibly taste any better but then a fe moments later begin to doubt that. 

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<cSSS> Black Garlic Butter basted Doubt Trout</c>

Before you is a fruit salad that looks too good for even a childrens picture book. Each piece of fruit is riped to perfection and of a bright, saturated, flawless color and shape.

After eating it, the eaters own colors become brighter and more saturated for a time.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<cþ  >Sweet</c> <cþþ >Shillering</c> <c þ >Rainbow</c> <c  þ>Salad</c>

Mango, passion fruit and a hint of honey are easily identified in this amazing drink. Something however gives it an interesting glittering shimmer and an extra kick. Likely something unique to Faerie since, try as you might, you have no idea what it may be.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<cþþ >Golden Glimmer</c>

A small cake, golden in color and topped with a small piece of honeycomb. The center of the cake is filled with liquid, warm honey and has a single Protea flower petal suspended in it. Biting into the cake, fills your whole mouth with the delicious, smooth sweetness of the honey until you reach the petal. The moment the tongue touches it, the incredible contrasting spicy nature of the petal rounds up the whole experience of tasting this treat. . 

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.

These are fried and diced mushrooms which have a golden sheen to their flesh. They have been placed on flatbread along with a red grass called Mithrenfire. Finally it has been sprinkled with cheese and lightly toasted. 

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.
<cÿÓ'>Gentle-Fried Golden Mushrooms on Flat Bread</c>

About the size and the same shape of a real unicorn horn, this hard candy has the same lovely twist and twirl. The flavor is vaguely comparable to honey, but even sweeter and smoother once it touches your tongue.

It is so rich in sweetness that those not used to feyfood or being feyblooded themselves can fall into a sugar-coma for a few hours.
<cÿÓ'>Hard Candy Honey Flavored Unicorn Horn</c>

An incredibly refreshing drink. Those with a keen sense can clearly taste lychee, dragonfruit and the faintest hint of coconut water.

Like most foods found in Faerie, they are extremely lavish and rich in flavor. There is nothing that can compare to it on the material plane.

This widget can be used to set a dynamic model's phenotype (PC or NPC) to any desired.

Use the Commands:
SetVarInt base_phenotype ## to set what the PC will turn back into. This will usually be 0 (for normal).

SetVarInt alt_phenotype ## to set what the PC will turn into. Example: SetVarInt alt_phenotype 19 will set the arcane "hovering" phenotype.

SetVarString phenotype_name to give a custom name to the phenotype. Example: Drow-Levitation

## Represents the numerical value of the phenotype. This is found in phenotype.2da or on the forums.
